      • Canonicalize

        @Namespace(value="arrow::dataset")
 @ByVal
public static ExpressionResult Canonicalize(@ByVal
                                                                                       Expression arg0,
                                                                                       ExecContext arg1)
        \defgroup expression-passes Functions for modification of Expressions \{ These transform bound expressions. Some transforms utilize a guarantee, which is provided as an Expression which is guaranteed to evaluate to true. The guaranteed_true_predicate need not be bound, but canonicalization is currently deferred to producers of guarantees. For example in order to be recognized as a guarantee on a field value, an Expression must be a call to "equal" with field_ref LHS and literal RHS. Flipping the arguments, "is_in" with a one-long value_set, ... or other semantically identical Expressions will not be recognized.

        Weak canonicalization which establishes guarantees for subsequent passes. Even equivalent Expressions may result in different canonicalized expressions. TODO this could be a strong canonicalization
